Keith Rodden will be the new crew chief for Austin Dillon and the #3 RCR car. He has been working for Chevy in their motorsports division after previously serving as a crew chief for McMurray at Ganassi and Kahne at Hendrick. Austin Hill will drive the Beard #62 in six races (both of the races at Daytona and Talladega as the team usually runs as well as the Chicago Street Course and Michigan). I think he's a perfect fit for that car as he's already a Chevy driver and is great at superspeedways!

Chad Johnston will be the crew chief of the SHR #41 car in 2023. Johnston was previously the crew chief of the DGR (now TRICON) #17 in the Truck Series which was driven part-time by Preece in 2022 so he will continue to work with Preece in 2023. Also, Johnston is returning to SHR as he was Tony Stewart's crew chief on the #14 car in 2014 and 2015.
